	<Title>
		Skip booze for better sleep
	</Title>
	<Body>
		&lt;p&gt;Alcohol depresses the central nervous system and acts as a sedative. It may help you fall asleep, but it prevents deeper stages of sleep and often causes you to wake up in the middle of the night. If you have trouble falling or staying asleep, say no thanks to the after-dinner drinks.&lt;/p&gt;
	</Body>
